# Failures Log - AI Self-Improvement Digest

## Known Issues

### Rate Limiting (429 errors)
**Problem:** Hitting Brave Search rate limits when scanning 6+ sources in one run  
**Root Cause:** Not respecting 10s delays between searches  
**Solution:** Add explicit wait(10000) between web_search calls; batch similar searches  
**Prevention:** Max 5 searches per batch, then 2-minute break  

### Duplicate Detection
**Problem:** Same article appears on consecutive days  
**Root Cause:** Deduplication check only looked at exact URL match, not URL variations or rewrites  
**Solution:** Implement title + domain fuzzy matching in deduplication step  
**Prevention:** Before posting, check both URL and title against posted list  

### Irrelevant Content Slip-Through
**Problem:** General AI news (e.g., "OpenAI releases new model") mixed into digest  
**Root Cause:** Filtering criteria too loose; didn't apply strict "self-improvement" test  
**Solution:** Add secondary filter: "Does this directly help James improve a core skill?" If no, exclude  
**Prevention:** Re-read STEP 3 filtering rules before posting  

### Setup Review Too Vague
**Problem:** Suggestions like "could consider exploring memory patterns"  
**Root Cause:** Not grounding suggestions in actual article findings  
**Solution:** For each suggestion, quote the specific article/pattern that inspired it  
**Prevention:** Mandatory rule: Every setup suggestion must reference a specific article  

### Source Unavailability
**Problem:** Anthropic.com engineering blog is down; entire run fails  
**Root Cause:** No graceful fallback for unavailable sources  
**Solution:** Skip and note in memory; continue with other Tier 1/2 sources  
**Prevention:** Try/catch around each source check; log failures but don't abort  

### Missing Context on X/Twitter
**Problem:** X searches don't fetch full context; quoted tweets are cut off  
**Root Cause:** Using basic web_search instead of x-research skill  
**Solution:** Use x-research skill when available for richer Twitter context  
**Prevention:** Document x-research setup as optional enhancement  

## Lessons Learned

- **Deduplication is critical:** One duplicate per week is 1/5 of the digest being garbage
- **Rate limits are real:** Always respect 10s between searches; batch similar work
- **Filtering saves time:** Strict criteria upfront beats weak filters that need manual review
- **Setup Review connects theory to practice:** Vague suggestions waste everyone's time; ground them in findings
- **Graceful degradation:** Sources go down; skip them and continue rather than aborting

